The paper deals with visual relationship detection (VRD) and scene graph generation, which are both tasks related to computer vision and image understanding. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of textual data to improve VRD performance, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) community, represented by cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper proposes a new deep model that relies on a shared text-image representation, which involves learning representations of objects and their interactions, and this could be relevant to the fields of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of text originating from images and books, which suggests that it could also be relevant to Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
